To get the postgres image from https://hub.docker.com/_/postgres

  docker pull postgres:version

to start the instance

  docker run --name some-postgres -e POSTGRES_PASSWORD=password -d -p 5432:5432 postgres

to use the interactive mode in postgresql

   docker exec -it postgres-0 bash

   to log in psql

    psql -U postgres
==>> now you coulld mange your data base with terminal


To get the pgAdmin with postgres using the compose
 and to stop the containers

 docker container stop container-id
  docker container rm container-id


deploy the compose on docker with

  docker-compose -f .\postgres-compos.yml up

